    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Does China Deserve Trade Status?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Butch Clark letter ridicules notion that China will change with permament trading status (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>What makes Samuel R. Berger and Gene Sperling (Op-Ed, May 19) think that permanent normal trading privileges will improve the chance for change in China? China can keep control of the populace even with a thriving economy. More money simply gives the government more resources to watch more closely and act faster. Economic strength means more military might. This is just one more way that China has outsmarted us again.</p>
        <p>BUTCH CLARK  Brooklyn, May 19, 2000</p>
      </block>
